<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-14T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-14T07:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2104: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-14T13:00:00+01:00">October 14, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 14—11:10 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>197. Sze called on me this morning and said that statements were
                            emanating from various quarters that China was negotiating directly with
                            Japan or was willing to undertake such negotiations. He asked me if I
                            would transmit to you his categorical denial of such statements or such
                            intentions on the part of China.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>